{% submission %}

{% submission-part type="problem" %}

Practicing for the STAAR but that would translate to facts and concepts. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% submission-part type="proposed-solution" %}

I teach U.S. History in Texas and would love an app that has all the STAAR EOC questions that have ever been given in one app.They could be categorized by subject, then grade levers, and then in my case for U.S. History by era, but also have a search by topic/keyword, and students can see those questions grouped by era, topic, or mixed if they choose. They could also do flashcards, play heads-up games, be quizzed (choose the type of quiz they want to build—pick the number of questions, topics/mixed, timed, etc.), compete with others, etc. Just a one-stop shop for all things U.S. History. It could also translate into multiple languages, include videos of topics bringing history to life, have an embedded dictionary of terms, and AI to grade and give feedback on short answers. You could also build the same for other tested subjects like English (have an embedded AI to grade short answers and essays), Biology, and Algebra (videos showing step by step how to solve a problem). The possibilities are endless. I want them to be able to learn, study, and then get data/results to track how they are doing and improving. So they can see if they are ready (Approved, Meets, or Masters) or if they need improvement (Does Not Meet) long before they take the test. Thanks for helping me with this. 

{% /submission-part %}

{% /submission %}